<paragraph id="CBDDC119B678540B79747009A44F8E81" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="198C042DF9B36B9A1419DDC7FD673581" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Among congeners of the orbitalis group, this species is distinguished by characters of the male terminalia as follows: Area between anterior arms of the hypandrium membranous; the ventral margin of the epandrium is gradually tapered to apex; the hypandrium is large and more heavily sclerotized (Figs 104-107).</paragraph>
